@Node "Introduction" "Post.guide/Introduction"
@Next "Installation"
@Prev "Legal Stuff"
@Toc "Main"

Introduction
************

   Post is a PostScript viewer using the post.library. The user can
view PostScript documents on screen, print them on any preferences
supported printer or create an IFF-ILBM file. It has a powerful CLI,
Workbench and ARexx interface.

   This documentation only provides information for the usage of Post.
If you need information about the library, fonts and so on you have to
rely on the documentation supplied with the library!


 @{" Features                  " Link "Features"}  
 @{" Requirements              " Link "Requirements"} 


@EndNode

@Node "Features" "Post.guide/Features"
@Next "Requirements"
@Toc "Introduction"

Features
========

   * Works on public screens, custom screens and even (some)
     graphiccards

   * Arexx port

   * Bandrendering

   * Both a Shell and Workbench interface

   * Keyboard and mouse control

   * ASL file and screenmode requesters

   * Uses OS 3.0 features like Pen-Sharing, ...


@EndNode

@Node "Requirements" "Post.guide/Requirements"
@Prev "Features"
@Toc "Introduction"

Requirements
============

   Post itself does not require much:

   * OS 2.0 or higher.

   * A post.library. The old post.library (V 1.7 (C) Adrian Aylward) or
     the new HWG post.library ((C) Heinz Wrobel) will do. Both are on
     the aminet (`text/print').

   * An assign to the drawer where Post lives in.

   But please keep in mind that the libraries tend to consume lots of
RAM and CPU power.


@EndNode

@Node "Installation" "Post.guide/Installation"
@Next "Usage"
@Prev "Introduction"
@Toc "Main"

Installation
************

   Just extract the lha-file to a temporary drawer of your joice.  I
assume that you have an installed post.library (V1.7, (C) Adrian
Aylward or HWG post.library, (C) Heinz Wrobel) and the version of Post
that comes with it. If you want to keep this old version rename it. You
might also want to make a backup of the file `init.ps'.  Then copy all
you want from the temporary post drawer to the old post drawer (the
only thing that is not obsolete is Post :-), but I suggest to keep all
files but the source drawer if you are not interested in the source) If
you use hwgpost.library you MUST NOT copy the file `init.ps'. The
version that comes with Post is only a bugfix for the one of Post
V1.86enh.  Copy the contents of the drawer envarc to envarc:. Delete
the temporary drawer. Make an assign POST: to your post drawer if you
don't already have one (best to do in the user-startup). That's all,
Post should run now.


@EndNode

