@Node "CLI-Interface" "Post.guide/CLI-Interface"
@Next "WB-Interface"
@Toc "Usage"

CLI-Interface
=============

   Post accepts many Options. Here is the template with description:

   * STARTUP-FILES/M: One or more startup-files to be used.

   * X-PAGESIZE=X/K/N, Y-PAGESIZE=Y/K/N, X-OFFSET=XOFF/K/N, Y-OFFSET=
     YOFF/K/N: The dimension and offset of the page.

   * X-DENSITY=XDEN/K/N, Y-DENSITY=YDEN/K/N, DENSITY=DEN/K/N: Density
     in x and y direction. Use DEN if you want to set both to the same
     value.

   * BW/S, RGB/S, CMYK/S: Color model to be used.

   * FONTMEM/K/N, HALFTONEMEM/K/N, VIRTUALMEM/K/N, LINEMEM/K/N: See
     documentation of the post.library.

   * BANDSIZE/K/N: See @{"Bandrendering" Link "Bandrendering"}

   * IFF-FILE=IFF/K: If specified Post will save the PostScript file as
     an IFF-ILBM file. For example:
          IFF path/iff*.pic  : path/iff1.pic,  path/iff2.pic  ...
          IFF path/iff??.pic : path/iff01.pic, path/iff02.pic ...
     NOTE: IFF path/iff.pic genearates only one IFF-ILBM file that
     contains the last page.

   * PRINTER/S: Output will go to the printer. See @{"Printing hints" Link "Printing hints"}.

   * FILE/K: The PostScript file to display, print or save as IFF-ILBM
     file.

   * FROM/K/N, TO/K/N: See @{"Bandrendering" Link "Bandrendering"}

   * NOFORMFEED/S, CENTERPAGE/S, PRINT-DENSITY=PRDEN/K/N: Print options.

   * TEMPPATH/K, BUFSIZE/K/N: Before a PostScript file is interpreted
     Post tries to split it (See @{"Bandrendering" Link "Bandrendering"}). TEMPPATH specifies the
     path where the temporary files are stored (should be in RAM: for
     speed benifits). If you have to choose a disk as destination due
     to memory limitations BUFSIZE should be set to a higher value than
     1024.

   * GRAPHICCARD/S: Sometimes it helps to work with graphiccards but
     costs one more bitplane (See @{"Technical Info" Link "Technical Info"}).

   * VERBOSE/S, CONWIN/S: Post will print out more messages if VERBOSE
     is specified. Output will go to STDERR if Post prints out a page or
     generates an IFF-ILBM file (useful for batch processing).
     Otherwise (or with CONWIN) output goes to the console window Post
     opens for I/O.

   * CUSTOMSCREEN/S, PUBSCREEN/K: Self explaining.

   * OPTFILE/K: Post will use this options file.

   When Post is started it uses its default options, then searches for
the options file (in ENVARC:) and then interprets options given in the
command list. When you quit Post it stores the options for the next
session (like `Options Use'). If you want to make things permanent just
save the options before you quit.


@EndNode

@Node "WB-Interface" "Post.guide/WB-Interface"
@Next "The Options Window"
@Prev "CLI-Interface"
@Toc "Usage"

WB-Interface
============

   Post can be run by double-clicking on its icon or by clicking on the
icon of Post and then double-clicking the icon of the file to be
displayed.  Following tooltypes are supported:
IFF, PRINTER, STARTUP-FILES, VERBOSE, NOFORMFEED, CENTERPAGE,
CUSTOMSCREEN, PUBSCREEN, X, Y, BANDSIZE, XOFF, YOFF, XDEN, YDEN, DEN,
PRDEN, BW, RGB, CMYK, FONTMEM, HALFETONMEM, VIRTUALMEM, LINEMEM,
TEMPPATH, BUFSIZE, GRAPHICCARD.
See @{"CLI-Interface" Link "CLI-Interface"} for discription.


@EndNode

@Node "The Options Window" "Post.guide/The Options Window"
@Next "ARexx-Interface"
@Prev "WB-Interface"
@Toc "Usage"

The Options Window
