Technical Info
==============

   The source is split up in several files and almost not documented but
there are many small functions that are self explaining. Post was
compiled with gcc 2.7.2.1.


@EndNode

@Node "History" "Post.guide/History"
@Next "Known Bugs"
@Prev "Technical Info"
@Toc "Miscellaneous"

History
=======

   When I first saw Post V1.86enh I was disappointed because of the poor
CLI and Workbench interface, the missing ARexx-Port, the nasty GUI ...
and after a look at ghostscript and PostView I decided to improve Post
V1.86enh.  But unfortunately the TODO list grew even faster on bottom
than it was shrunk on top. Therefore, because of lack of time and
because of my programming style (which caused lack of documentation)
history is rather rudimentary up to Post V2.00 as you can see below :-).

   History starts here:

   * Post V2.00: first public release


@EndNode

@Node "Known Bugs" "Post.guide/Known Bugs"
@Next "To Do"
@Prev "History"
@Toc "Miscellaneous"

Known bugs
==========

   * Post complains that it can't get the colors on a pubscreen in CMYK
     mode although there are enough colors: this is no bug. Post tries
     to obtain colors with ObtainPen but the colors needed for CMYK on
     a pubscreen are obtained by the mouse pointer and therefore not
     free.

   * With HWG post.library the current directory cannot be changed and
     therefore files that are loaded via `(files.ps) run, ...' are not
     found.

   * Post uses the feature of the OS that a plane pointer with value -1
     is interpreted like a plane with all pixels set. Some graphic
     cards do not support this and you have to specify GRAPHICCARD.
     Then a plane will be allocated and all pixels are set in it
     (needless to say that this is a waste of memory :-) But still some
     graphiccards don't work and I need help here 'cause I don't own
     one by myself!


@EndNode

